<TITLE> Govt will punish graft confessors: Shafiq </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 31 (bdnews24.com)  The government will punish public servants who confessed to corruption in exchange for clemency from the Truth and Accountability Commission under the past caretaker government, the law minister said Tuesday. "No corrupt government employees or officials will be allowed to remain in service," Shafiq Ahmed told reporters at the secretariat. "A committee to probe the charges will be formed and departmental measures will be taken against those who confessed and received clemency from the Truth Commission." The commission awarded certificates of clemency to around 351 government employees in total after TAC hearings. bdn
